                            <comment id="12899354" author="sammychen" created="Tue, 17 Aug 2010 09:16:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;using gcc4.3+ ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12905337" author="bryanduxbury" created="Thu, 2 Sep 2010 00:22:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;When I do &quot;make -C lib/cpp&quot;, I get an error with or without the attached patch applied, so I don&apos;t feel comfortable applying this patch. Anyone with CPP experience want to weigh in on whether this should be committed?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12905544" author="dreiss" created="Thu, 2 Sep 2010 15:21:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s definitely an improvement.  We might also need to change &quot;malloc&quot; and &quot;free&quot; to &quot;std::malloc&quot; and &quot;std::free&quot; for maximum compatibility.  (Or add &quot;using std::malloc;&quot;).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12905582" author="bryanduxbury" created="Thu, 2 Sep 2010 16:44:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I just committed this. (If we want to make the changes David suggested, we can apply on a follow-on patch.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
